ce:section.ce:para:
The alkali lignin was rinsed repeatedly and then desiccated in a drying cabinet at 60 °C for 72 h. We used all kinds of chemical reagents in the analytical grade or best available grade (
                        supporting information S1.1
                     ). A series of techniques was carried out to characterize the structure of purified lignin (
                        supporting information S1.2
                     ). The extraction of lignin-based GCDs and RCDs was achieved by the solvothermal reaction and subsequent biphasic fractionation. The Co-N-C biochar was prepared via the direct calcination of residual lignin, cobalt nitrate, KHCO3 and urea. Afterwards, the ultrasound-aided assembly of dot-sheet-heterostructured Co-N-C@CDs was conducted by uniformly dispersing RCDs and Co-N-C in water (
                        supporting information S1.3
                     ). The morphology, microstructure, elemental analysis, surface chemical states, specific surface area, and electrochemical measurements of Co-N-C@CDs were performed to evaluate their performances of CDI and ZIHCs (
                        supporting information S1.4
                     ).
